First of all, you need to register your reCAPTCHA V3 and get the keys (siteKey and secretKey).

With the keys in hand, you need to load the follows javascript:

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js?render=reCAPTCHA_site_key&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

Call grecaptcha.execute on an action or when the page loads

        &lt;script&gt;
      grecaptcha.ready(function() {
          grecaptcha.execute(&#39;reCAPTCHA_site_key&#39;, {action: &#39;homepage&#39;}).then(function(token) {
             ...
          });
      });
      &lt;/script&gt;


The grecaptcha.execute with return a token, so you need to send the token to your backend with the request to verify the reCAPTCHA. (https://developers.google.com/recaptcha/docs/verify)

Be careful with the follow token restrictions

